# CPT CSV Template

Each row: variable, parent1, parent2, ..., state, probability

For discrete variable with parents:
```csv
variable,parent1,parent2,state,probability
grasp_stability,cube_weight,surface_friction,low,0.1
grasp_stability,cube_weight,surface_friction,medium,0.3
grasp_stability,cube_weight,surface_friction,high,0.6
grasp_stability,cube_weight,surface_friction,low,0.4
# ... all combinations of parent states
```

For variable without parents (prior):
```csv
variable,state,probability
task_context,clean,0.5
task_context,cluttered,0.3
task_context,dynamic,0.15
task_context,constrained,0.05
```

For continuous variable (discretized):
```csv
variable,bin,probability
cube_weight,0,0.1
cube_weight,1,0.2
cube_weight,2,0.4
cube_weight,3,0.2
cube_weight,4,0.1
```

---

## Example: pick_place_outcome CPT

```csv
# grasp_stability depends on cube_weight (3 bins), surface_friction (3 bins), gripper_force (3 bins)
# 3x3x3 = 27 parent combinations x 3 states = 81 rows
variable,cube_weight_bin,friction_bin,force_bin,state,probability
grasp_stability,0,0,0,low,0.6
grasp_stability,0,0,0,medium,0.3
grasp_stability,0,0,0,high,0.1
grasp_stability,0,0,1,low,0.3
grasp_stability,0,0,1,medium,0.4
grasp_stability,0,0,1,high,0.3
# ... etc

# success depends on grasp_stability
variable,grasp_stability,state,probability
success,low,fail,0.8
success,low,succeed,0.2
success,medium,fail,0.3
success,medium,succeed,0.7
success,high,fail,0.05
success,high,succeed,0.95
```

